    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="715"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d715">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 EAC/11: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-22">November 22,
                            1943</date>.<lb/>[Received November 23—1:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2012. <hi rend="italic">Pravda</hi> for November 22nd carried an announcement of
                    the appointment of the principal representative of the USSR on the European
                    Advisory Commission reading as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“In accordance with the decision of the Moscow Conference regarding the
                            establishment in London of the European Advisory Commission the Soviet
                            Government has appointed as principal representative of the Soviet Union
                            on this Commission the Ambassador of the USSR in Great Britain Comrade
                            F. T. Gusev.”<note n="14" xml:id="d715fn14">Feodor Tarasoviteh
                                Gousev.</note>
                        </p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
